So nodejs is basically the browser engine for your code editor so you can use the Javascript for the backend and make a server.js file where you can write all your backend stuff moreover for adding any node modules or any other persons code you can use npm 
By using npm init you can make a package.json file where all the info regarding the entry file or the dependencies are there
you can use npm install #nameofthelibrary and then enter and all the nodemodules regarding that will be installed.
